MINSTRETLunknown12'hb02

MINSTRETL (RW) 31:0 : Lower Instruction retired count From the spec "Some CSRs, such as the instructions retired counter, instret, may be modified as side effects of instruction execution. In these cases, if a CSR access instruction reads a CSR, it reads the value prior to the execution of the instruction. If a CSR access instruction writes a CSR, the update occurs after the execution of the instruction. In particular, a value written to instret by one instruction will be the value read by the following instruction (i.e., the increment of instret caused by the first instruction retiring happens before the write of the new value)."
